vdsx1CardTable.name: vdsx1CardTable
vdsx1CardTable.description: The Vertical DS1 Configuration table extension.

vdsx1CardEntry.name: vdsx1CardEntry
vdsx1CardEntry.description: An entry in the Vertical Card Configuration table (an extension to the rfc1406 Configuration table.

vdsx1cardSlotNumber.name: vdsx1cardSlotNumber
vdsx1cardSlotNumber.description: Physical slot in the system in which the card is installed.

vdsx1cardType.name: vdsx1cardType
vdsx1cardType.description: The Vertical's card Type. The following types are defined: cardTYPE-DUAL-T1 = 1, cardTYPE-8-CHANNEL-CO-POTS = 3, cardTYPE-BRIDGE1 = 4, cardTYPE-NOT-CONFIGURED = 100

vdsx1cardIOPortAddress.name: vdsx1cardIOPortAddress
vdsx1cardIOPortAddress.description: The ISA bus base address for this Card.

vdsx1cardErrorLED.name: vdsx1cardErrorLED
vdsx1cardErrorLED.description: All Vertical cards have an ERROR LED and a READY LED. The combined values of these LEDs are as follows - ERRORLed READYLed VALUE OPERATIONAL DEFINITION OFF OFF (0 0) Invalid state ON OFF (1 0) Just after power up. This state remains until card is ready to service io. ON ON (1 1) Statue during software initialization OFF ON (0 1) The normal operational state of the card.

vdsx1cardReadyLED.name: vdsx1cardReadyLED
vdsx1cardReadyLED.description: All Vertical cards have a READY LED and an ERROR LED. The combined values of these LEDs are as follows - ERRORLed READYLed OPERATIONAL DEFINITION OFF OFF invalid state ON OFF Just after power up. This state remains until card is ready to service io. ON ON Statue during software initialization OFF ON The normal operational state of the card.

vdsx1TrunkTable.name: vdsx1TrunkTable
vdsx1TrunkTable.description: The DS1 Trunk table extensions for Vertical Networks Instant Office.

vdsx1TrunkEntry.name: vdsx1TrunkEntry
vdsx1TrunkEntry.description: An entry in the Vertical DS1 Trunk table

vdsx1TrunkIfIndex.name: vdsx1TrunkIfIndex
vdsx1TrunkIfIndex.description: The interface Index for this trunk. The value for this object is equal to the value of dsx1IfIndex from the Interfaces table of DS1/E1 (RFC 1406). Which also correlates to the IfIndex found in MIB-II.

vdsx1TrunkIndex.name: vdsx1TrunkIndex
vdsx1TrunkIndex.description: This object is the index into the number of trunks associated with the card defined in the card group.

vdsx1TrunkIdentifier.name: vdsx1TrunkIdentifier
vdsx1TrunkIdentifier.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of dsx1CircuitIdentifier from the Configuration table of DS1/E1 (RFC 1406). This is a vendor specific field used to help identify each specific interface for diagnostic purposes.

vdsx1TrunkSlotNumber.name: vdsx1TrunkSlotNumber
vdsx1TrunkSlotNumber.description: The value for this object is the logical number of the slot in which the card containing this trunk is located, (vdsx1cardSlotNumber).

vdsx1TrunkDeviceNumber.name: vdsx1TrunkDeviceNumber
vdsx1TrunkDeviceNumber.description: The value for this object is the logical device number of this trunk within its slot. This number may be used to identify this device in the registry.

vdsx1TrunkInterrupt.name: vdsx1TrunkInterrupt
vdsx1TrunkInterrupt.description: Interrupt Request level for this card/trunk. Note: all trunks in the same card have the same IRQ.

vdsx1TrunkEnabled.name: vdsx1TrunkEnabled
vdsx1TrunkEnabled.description: Setting this variable to Deactivated will disable this particular trunk.

vdsx1TrunkMasterPriority.name: vdsx1TrunkMasterPriority
vdsx1TrunkMasterPriority.description: Designates the priority for selecting which trunk is to drive the MVIP SEC8K clock, i.e. which trunk drives the master timing system. This value must be diffrent for each Trunk in the system.Valid values mean: notUsed (100)=> never choose this trunk as clock master primary (1)=> choose this trunk as first choice firstAlternate (2)=> choose this trunk as second choice secondAlternate (3)=> choose this trunk as third choice

vdsx1TrunkStream.name: vdsx1TrunkStream
vdsx1TrunkStream.description: The MVIP Stream assigned to the Trunk.

vdsx1TrunkStartingChannel.name: vdsx1TrunkStartingChannel
vdsx1TrunkStartingChannel.description: The starting MVIP channel within the MVIP Stream. If CardType is DTM or WAN1, this value is 0; if CardType is CO-POTS, this value is 16 or 24.

vdsx1TrunkType.name: vdsx1TrunkType
vdsx1TrunkType.description: Specifies the TrunkType for this trunk. Defines E1 vs T1 as well as Common Channel Signalling (CCS) vs. Channel Associated Signalling (CAS). Valid values are : dev-undef, // 100 : undefined dev-t1CAS, // 1 : T1 Channel Associated Signaling dev-t1CCS, // 2 : T1 Common Channel Signaling : with D channel dev-coPots, // 7 : CO Pots (analog)

vdsx1TrunkIsdnSignalingProtocol.name: vdsx1TrunkIsdnSignalingProtocol
vdsx1TrunkIsdnSignalingProtocol.description: Defines the switch type for the Isdn protocol stack. The following are all the possible types: other(1), none of the following ess4(5), U.S.A. / AT&T 4ESS ess5(6), U.S.A. / AT&T 5ESS dms100(7), U.S.A. / Northern Telecom DMS100 ni2(10), U.S.A. / National ISDN 2 (BRI, PRI) dms100s100 (263) NT DMS-100 switch / S-100

vdsx1TrunkLineCoding.name: vdsx1TrunkLineCoding
vdsx1TrunkLineCoding.description: Line Coding, i.e. the zero code suppression used for this Trunk. Valid values are: b8ZS (2) -> use of a specified pattern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. aMI (5) -> a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present other (6) -> none of the codes described above, or Not Applicable, whichever is appropriate Presently, T1 trunk can be either b8zs (2) or ami (5). E1 trunk must be hdb3 (3).

vdsx1TrunkFraming.name: vdsx1TrunkFraming
vdsx1TrunkFraming.description: Defines framing for Trunk. T1 trunk can be either esf (2) or d4 (3). E1 trunk can be either e1-crc (5) or e1-mf (6). In cases where Framing is not applicable, value 1 (other) would be displayed.

vdsx1TrunkDChannelSlot.name: vdsx1TrunkDChannelSlot
vdsx1TrunkDChannelSlot.description: Slot number of trunk whose DChannel controls the B channels of this trunk.

vdsx1TrunkDChannelDevice.name: vdsx1TrunkDChannelDevice
vdsx1TrunkDChannelDevice.description: Specifies the device number of the trunk whose D channel controls the B channels of this trunk.

vdsx1TrunkNumberOfChannels.name: vdsx1TrunkNumberOfChannels
vdsx1TrunkNumberOfChannels.description: Maximum number of channels to be initialized for this trunk - 0..24 for T1, 0..31 for E1, 0..8 for COPots.

vdsx1TrunkLineBuildOut.name: vdsx1TrunkLineBuildOut
vdsx1TrunkLineBuildOut.description: Defines the line build out option. The following are applicable values : buildOut-minus15dB , i.e. -15 dB (1), buildOut-0dB , i.e. 0 dB (2), buildOut-minus7point5dB , i.e. -7.5 db (3) .

vdsx1TrunkLoopback.name: vdsx1TrunkLoopback
vdsx1TrunkLoopback.description: This variable represents the loopback confi- guration of the DS1 interface. Agents support- ing read/write access should return badValue in response to a requested loopback state that the interface does not support. The values mean: vdsx1NoLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. vdsx1PayloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for re- transmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. vdsx1LineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum pene- tration) but is looped back out. vdsx1OtherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here.

vdsx1TrunkRedLED.name: vdsx1TrunkRedLED
vdsx1TrunkRedLED.description: Specifies the RED LED status of the trunk OFF = 0, ON = 1.

vdsx1TrunkYellowLED.name: vdsx1TrunkYellowLED
vdsx1TrunkYellowLED.description: Specifies the YELLOW LED status of the trunk OFF = 0, ON = 1.

vdsx1TrunkChangePending.name: vdsx1TrunkChangePending
vdsx1TrunkChangePending.description: Indicates that a change to the device values have been made to the registry. The intepretation of the values are : 1 => change made to the registry, but not incorporated in the device yet 0 => the device changes the value to 0 from 1, after it incorporates the value from registry.

vdsx1ChannelTable.name: vdsx1ChannelTable
vdsx1ChannelTable.description: Channel entries for each of the channels associated with each trunk defined in the trunk table.

vdsx1ChannelEntry.name: vdsx1ChannelEntry
vdsx1ChannelEntry.description: Each entry is one channel in a T1/E1 trunk.

vdsx1channelIndex.name: vdsx1channelIndex
vdsx1channelIndex.description: This is the logical channel number of the channel within its trunk. For T1 it is between 1 and 24 for E1 it is between 1 and 32.

vdsx1channelTrunkIndex.name: vdsx1channelTrunkIndex
vdsx1channelTrunkIndex.description: This is the index of the trunk (relative to its card) to which this channel belongs.

vdsx1channelSlotNumber.name: vdsx1channelSlotNumber
vdsx1channelSlotNumber.description: The value for this object is the logical number of the slot in which the card (and trunk) containing is located (vdsx1cardSlotNumber)..

vdsx1channelTrunkDeviceNumber.name: vdsx1channelTrunkDeviceNumber
vdsx1channelTrunkDeviceNumber.description: The value for this object is the logical device number of the trunk containing this channel within its slot, ie vdsx1TrunkDeviceNumber

vdsx1channelEnabled.name: vdsx1channelEnabled
vdsx1channelEnabled.description: Setting this variable to Deactivated will disable this particular channel. Valid values are : vdsx1channelDeactivated (100) vdsx1channelActivated (1) vdsx1channelNotConfigured (2)

vdsx1channelType.name: vdsx1channelType
vdsx1channelType.description: Channel type, vdsx1channelTypeUnknown : Unknown type vdsx1channelTypeWink : E&M (Ear and Mouth) start vdsx1channelTypeGS : Ground Start Digital trunk. vdsx1channelTypeClear : Nailed up clear channel, for data vdsx1channelTypeAnalogImm: Analog Trunk, Immediate start vdsx1channelTypeBChan: PRI B channel on T1 or E1 vdsx1channelTypeDChan: PRI D channel on T1 or E1 vdsx1channelTypeAnalogDt: Analog channel, dialtone start vdsx1channelTypeAnalogGs: Analog channel, ground start vdsx1channelTypeDDS: DDS channel (56K or 64K) vdsx1channelTypeAnalogDID: Analog channel, DID wink

vdsx1channelState.name: vdsx1channelState
vdsx1channelState.description: The Call State of this particular channel. Valid values are : Out of Service (channelStateOOS - 1), Idle (channelStateIdle - 2), InBound Call (channelStateInCall - 3), OutBound Call (channelStateOutCall - 4), Off line (channelStateOffline - 5), Other state (channelStateOther - 6), Data (channelStateData - 7), Error (channelStateError - 8), Ringing Far End (channelStateFeRinging - 9), Incoming Ringing (channelStateNeRinging - 10), Sending Digits (channelStateDigitSend - 11), Receiving Digits (channelStateDigitRcv - 12), Incall Established (channelStateIncallEst - 13), Outcall Established (channelStateOutcallEst - 14), Incall Clearing (channelStateIncallClear - 15), Outcall Clearing (channelStateOutcallClear - 16).

vdsx1channelCallerID.name: vdsx1channelCallerID
vdsx1channelCallerID.description: The callerID of an incoming caller, if available. If the callerID is not available, then it will have a length of zero

vdsx1channelExternalAddress.name: vdsx1channelExternalAddress
vdsx1channelExternalAddress.description: The far end number of a connected call on this channel.If the number is not available, then it will have a length of zero.

vdsx1channelExternalSubAddress.name: vdsx1channelExternalSubAddress
vdsx1channelExternalSubAddress.description: The far end sub address of a connected call on this channel.If this is not available, then it will have a length of zero

vdsx1channelLocalAddress.name: vdsx1channelLocalAddress
vdsx1channelLocalAddress.description: The local number of a connected call on this channel.If the number is not available, then it will have a length of zero

vdsx1channelLocalSubAddress.name: vdsx1channelLocalSubAddress
vdsx1channelLocalSubAddress.description: The local sub address of a connected call on this channel.If the number is not available, then it will have a length of zero

vdsx1channelChangePending.name: vdsx1channelChangePending
vdsx1channelChangePending.description: Indicates that a change to the channel values have been made to the registry. The intepretation of the values are : 1 => change made to the registry, but not incorporated in the device yet 0 => the device changes the value to 0 from 1, after it incorporates the value from registry.

vdsx1TrunkRedClear.name: vdsx1TrunkRedClear
vdsx1TrunkRedClear.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk RED alarm condition clears.

vdsx1TrunkRed.name: vdsx1TrunkRed
vdsx1TrunkRed.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk goes into the RED alarm situation. Red alarm condition signifies LOS (Loss of Signal) failure, i.e. the receiver sees no positive or negative pulses

vdsx1TrunkYellowClear.name: vdsx1TrunkYellowClear
vdsx1TrunkYellowClear.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk YELLOW alarm condition clears.

vdsx1TrunkYellow.name: vdsx1TrunkYellow
vdsx1TrunkYellow.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk goes into the YELLOW alarm situation. Yellow alarm condition signifies a LOF (Loss of Frame) condition, i.e. the receiver does not see the expected framing pattern.

vdsx1TrunkBlueClear.name: vdsx1TrunkBlueClear
vdsx1TrunkBlueClear.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk BLUE alarm condition clears.

vdsx1TrunkBlue.name: vdsx1TrunkBlue
vdsx1TrunkBlue.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk goes into the BLUE alarm situation. Blue alarm conditions occurs when the source goes into AIS (Alarm indication Signal) state. This means that the source has a problem that prevents it from sending its normal, framed payload. Instead, it sends an unframed stream of 1's.

vdsx1TrunkReconfigComplete.name: vdsx1TrunkReconfigComplete
vdsx1TrunkReconfigComplete.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk successfully reads and incorporates the values from the registry. This is typically done in response to a SET command on any of the Trunk's (or its channel's) read-write parameters

vdsx1TrunkReconfigError.name: vdsx1TrunkReconfigError
vdsx1TrunkReconfigError.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk fails to incorporate the values read from the registry. Typically, the trunk tries to re-read the registry values in response to a SET command on any of the Trunk's (or its channel's) read-write parameters

vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOn.name: vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOn
vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOn.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk enters a payload loopback state. Payload loopback means that the received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for re- transmission after it has passed through the device's framing function

vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOff.name: vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOff
vdsx1TrunkLoopbackPayloadOff.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk moves from a payload loopback state to a non loopback state.

vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOn.name: vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOn
vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOn.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk enters a line loopback state. Under this state the received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out.

vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOff.name: vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOff
vdsx1TrunkLoopbackLineOff.description: This notification is sent when the specific trunk goes out of a Line Looped state
